                    <!-- Introduction -->
                    <section id="introduction">
                        <h2>Why Subtitle Translation Matters More Than Ever</h2>
                        <p>Video content is global. A YouTube tutorial filmed in English can reach viewers in Tokyo, Sao Paulo, and Berlin&mdash;but only if those viewers can understand it. Subtitle translation is no longer a luxury reserved for Hollywood studios. It is a competitive advantage for independent creators, course sellers, marketers, and businesses of every size.</p>
                        <p>The numbers speak for themselves. Videos with translated subtitles see an average 15% increase in watch time across non-native audiences. YouTube channels that add multilingual subtitles report up to 3x growth in international subscribers. For e-learning platforms, translated subtitles are often a legal accessibility requirement in the European Union and beyond.</p>
                        <p>The challenge has always been cost and time. Professional human translation can run $5 to $15 per minute of video, per language. Translate a 20-minute video into five languages and you are looking at $500 to $1,500. AI-powered subtitle translation tools have changed this equation dramatically, bringing costs down to a fraction while delivering surprisingly good quality.</p>
                        <p>In this guide we compare three leading AI subtitle translation tools: <strong>SubWhisper Pro</strong>, <strong>VEED</strong>, and <strong>Kapwing</strong>. We have tested all three extensively across multiple languages and video types to give you an honest, detailed comparison.</p>
                    </section>

                    <!-- Quick Comparison Table -->
                    <section id="quick-comparison">
                        <h2>Quick Comparison: SubWhisper Pro vs VEED vs Kapwing</h2>
                        <p>Before diving into the details, here is a snapshot of how the three tools stack up on the metrics that matter most.</p>

